#  memo for installing postgresql version 8.3.1 using backports.
#                                     21-Jun-08   SM
#

- get newer version of Debian's postgres cluster manager and install
  them with dpkg,

 dpkg -i postgresql-client-common_88~bpo40+1_all.deb
 dpkg -i postgresql-common_88~bpo40+1_all.deb.deb

- put backports into /etc/apt/source.list by adding this line,

deb http://www.backports.org/debian/ etch-backports main contrib non-free

- update apt-get and get keyring by doing these,

 apt-get update 
 apt-get isntall debian-backports-keyring
 apt-get update

- install postgres version 8.3.1 client and server

 apt-get install postgresql-client-8.3 postgresql-8,3

- data will be stored into /var/lib/postgresql/<version #>/main and
  configuration files are stored in /etc/postgresql/<version #>/main
  directories. 
